model

Class RCNN_Model

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • model.RCNN_Model

  • public class RCNN_Model
extends java.util.Observable
    RCNN_Model is the model component of the MVC part of the RCNN visualization. It contains:
    • Persistent Node History
    • Forward Edge Information
    • Backward Edge Information
    Author:
    Alexander McArther

      • RCNN_Model

        public RCNN_Model(int nodeDataSize)
        Initializes the model of the RCNN Visualization. In the process it generates a LinkedHashMap for the node list.
        Parameters:
        nodeDataSize - - Integer specifying how many nodes states to store per node.

      • hasEdgeBetween

        public boolean hasEdgeBetween(java.lang.String parentName,
                     java.lang.String childName)
        Attempts to locate an edge in the forward edge map between the two input nodes.
        Parameters:
        parentName - - Name of the origin node.
        childName - - Name of the terminating node.
        Returns:
        true if the edge was found in the internal forward edge map, false otherwise.

      • updateNodeMap

        public void updateNodeMap(java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Float> newNodeData)
        Uses new input data in the form of a LinkedHashMap to update the model's version of the data. It adds nodes if they aren't already in the structure, and removes them if they weren't in this latest batch of data
        Parameters:
        newNodeData - - A LinkedHashMap containing string keys and float data elements corresponding to new data from some source
